The paper deals with the problem of person re-identification, which is a subfield of computer vision. The proposed method involves learning a distributional set distance function between two image sets, which requires knowledge of both appearance features and temporal information. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as these sub-categories are closely related to the proposed method. Additionally, the paper involves the use of Wasserstein distance, which is a popular tool in generative models and optimization, indicating that it may also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses public datasets to evaluate the proposed method, which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
